The Foreign Secretary is more likely to be in touch with ordinary people after she came out on top with 63 percent of Tory members agreeing she was "more in touch and trustworthy" in Monday night's debate. In the latest YouGov poll, only 19 percent of members voted for Mr Sunak, who was accused of being "pretty aggressive" during the debate by ally of Ms Truss, Simon Clarke. A total of 54 percent also said Ms Truss was more likable than her opponent. However, Mr Sunak did pip Ms truss to the post for coming across as more Prime Ministerial in the debate with 43 percent. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES... 